## ðŸ›¡ï¸ Quality & Best Practices

### Security

**Secrets & Configuration:**
- âŒ NEVER commit secrets to version control
- âœ… Use environment variables for sensitive data
- âœ… Use .env files for local development
- âœ… Rotate secrets regularly

**Input & Output:**
- âœ… Validate all user inputs at API boundaries
- âœ… Use DTOs with validation decorators
- âœ… Sanitize data before processing
- âœ… Escape output to prevent injection attacks

**Authentication & Authorization:**
- âœ… Use JWT tokens for authentication
- âœ… Implement proper authorization checks
- âœ… Use HTTPS in production
- âœ… Implement rate limiting to prevent abuse

**Data Protection:**
- âœ… Encrypt sensitive data at rest
- âœ… Use secure communication (HTTPS/TLS)
- âœ… Implement proper CORS policies
- âœ… Log security events for monitoring
- âŒ NEVER expose sensitive data in logs

### Performance

**Backend:**
- Use database indexing for frequently queried fields
- Implement caching for expensive operations
- Optimize database queries (avoid N+1 problems)
- Use pagination for large datasets
- Monitor query performance and optimize slow queries

**Frontend:**
- Optimize bundle sizes and use code splitting
- Implement lazy loading for routes and components
- Use efficient state management patterns
- Optimize images and assets
- Implement proper caching strategies

**Monitoring:**
- Monitor application performance with APM tools
- Set up performance alerts for critical metrics
- Track database performance and query times
- Monitor memory usage and garbage collection
- Use performance budgets for builds

**Scalability:**
- Design for horizontal scaling from the start
- Use stateless services when possible
- Implement proper caching layers
- Use CDN for static assets
- Plan for database scaling strategies

### Testing

**Coverage Requirements:**
- âœ… Write tests for all new code
- âœ… Backend: Unit tests (Jest)
- âœ… Frontend: Widget tests (Flutter Test)
- âŒ Frontend: NO end-to-end (e2e) tests

**Test Types:**
- **Unit tests**: Business logic, services, utilities
- **Integration tests**: API endpoints, database operations
- **Widget tests**: UI components, user interactions
- **Performance tests**: Load testing, benchmarks

